actual.comment:
1) Some identified gaps now narrowed down in Viet Nam: (i) regulations on controlling corruption/bribery in the private sector; (ii) regulations on controlling corruption involving foreign public officials;
2) 3 policy research papers commissioned and 3 high-level policy dialogues convened together with the Central Commission on Internal Affairs (which is under the Vietnam Communist Party Central Committee, and advisory body for the Politburo in anti-corruption) on three topics: (i) Enhancing Mechanisms in Handling Corruption Crimes and in Law Enforcement; ii) Improving Provisions in the Criminal Procedural Code to Effectively Detect and Handle Corruption Crimes in Viet Nam; and (iii) Ways Forward to Enhanced Enforcement of the Anti-corruption Law in Viet Nam; 
3) 3-very significant. UNDP’s recommendations on how to address gaps in prevention, investigation and prosecution of corruption were incorporated into the 2015 Amendment to the Penal Code (especially in liability of legal entities though not yet in corruption crime due to Viet Nam's reservation, in corruption in the private sector, and in bribing foreign public officials). In addition, findings from an evidence-based research on corruption in the public sector in Viet Nam using PAPI data used in the Government Inspectorate's report to the National Assembly, creating significant public interest.

1) 4 quality researches and knowledge products provided to National Assembly committees to inform the formulation of important laws such as Law on Election, Law on Laws, Law on Local Governance, Law on Family and Marriage Law, Criminal code, etc… These are:
- Guidelines on conducting legislative research in National Assembly bodies;
- Research on some issues on the Criminal Code in accordance with the Judicial Reform Strategy 
- Seminar on the Law on Election of Deputies to the National Assembly and People’s Council organized (with a focus on a new chapter on National Election Council)
- Field study and research on issues related to local government 
2) 2-significant. Law on Promulgation of Legal Documents was developed and approved with inputs from project's research.
3) 10 legislative information exchange events organized and publications developed, specifically: 
- A research and sensitizing workshop for members of parliament on the implementation of International Conventions on Human Rights to which Vietnam is a party;
- A strategy for ILS to meet the need for legislative information of NA committees and deputies;
- Publication of 6 current legislative bulletins and 2 special editions of legislation studies magazines

